what makes you cry i have been wondering about this question for a while now and not even my science teacher knew the answer description would be nice i mean what physically makes you cry like what signals tears in your body it all has to do with emotions that trigger tears first you have to use any of the five senses to see hear smell feel or taste something that really bothers you or makes you emotional then your nerves send the message to your brain that you are feeling bad your brain then releases anti depressant hormones endorphins the same ones released during aerobic exercise that make you feel so good and you have the uncontrollable urge to cry you're face tightens the tears cloud your vision you choke up you hiccup sob and you start crying amazingly enough crying actually makes you feel better ever noticed when you're done and that's the condensed version lol of what happens when you cry here's a tissue Brain Signal transduction Tears Panic attack Meditation Endorphin Self-harm Stroke Autism Clinical depression Sadism and masochism Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Human physiology Transsexuality Shaggy dog story Olfaction Glossary of medical terms related to communications disorders Muscle Cancer Drug addiction Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Hypoglycemia Inception of Darwin's theory The Amber Spyglass Social rule Psychosis Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Diabetes mellitus Pain Nervous system God Emperor of Dune Stem cell Consciousness Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Motivation Anger management Chronic fatigue syndrome The Parting of the Ways Head Breastfeeding Joke Asperger syndrome Sense Dualism (philosophy of mind) Medicine Yawn Orgasm Eye Cognitive science Human Chemotherapy Sensory Integration Dysfunction Laughter Weight training Babe Ruth Fibromyalgia Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Puberty Obsessive-compulsive disorder Internet troll Marie Antoinette Philosophy of mind Mojave people Hulk (comics) Anxiety Prostate cancer Main characte